Different projections around the photo of a casting by Rodin

*The way the light danced across the curves of the bronze figure, bringing out the subtle nuances of the sculptor's masterful hand. It was as if the very essence of the artist's vision had been distilled onto the page, waiting to be rediscovered by the viewer. The faint shadows cast by the model's features seemed to whisper secrets of the human form, drawing the eye inexorably to the subject.*
